Automation : 
- A process / system that can run by itself
- Run by itself
- Without human intervention

Benefits:
- Run Longer time
- Without/Less human intervention
- Lesser time to execute
- Reusability
- Nightly run, morning monitoring

When to do automation
- Stable
- Manually Passed
- Repeated Testing

XYZ-234
In Amazon there will be a tab called 'Medical Care & Pharmacy'.
Acceptance Criteria:
1. Hoverover on this tab will display a list of Medical Provider
2. Upon clickin a new page will appears in a new tab
3. There will be sub-menu of 'One Medical', 'Pharmacy', 'Clinic' and 'FSA|HSA Store'

Sprint 1, Sprint 2, Sprint 3
N-1:
Create Test Plan for Sprint 2
Execute Sprint 1 Testing
In-Sprint testing:
Create and Execute Test Plan in the same sprint

Automation Framework Types:
1. TDD - Test Driven Development - Selenium, TestNG/JUnit
2. BDD - Behavior Driven Development - Cucumber, Selenium, TestNG/JUnit
3. DDD - Data Driven Development - Apache POI, JDBC
4. MDD - Modular Driven Development
5. KDD - Keyword Driven Development
6. Linear - Linear Scripting
7. Hybrid - Combination of above

Automation Design patterns: (3000)
1. Creational (Page Object Model)
2. Behabioural (Singleton)
3. Structural (Builder)

Build Tools: Maven, Gradle
Goals:
- clean - cleaning the exisitng compilation files
- compile - parent.java > parent.class
- install - if depencies are not available in .m2, then it will download into local
- package - create a jar file of the whole project
- test - test will run tests
- verify - verify that required fileds are available to compile/deploy
- deploy - create a copy of code and run it in the given environment

- pom.xml - dependencies, dependency, plugins, build, dependency management

Project
- src
	- main
